Alexander Wang's designs have always been a bit casual, a bit masculine, and as of late, a bit sporty. And it seems he just keeps getting better, bringing all these elements and more to his latest 2013 Resort Collection.

 

Styling his simple, trademark pieces into a more couture territory, Alexander's newest collection is full of monochrome outfits perfect for packing. Each piece—from loose leather shorts and cropped slacks to sheer knee-length shift dresses—is beautiful enough to be worn to an afternoon cocktail party, yet comfortable enough for a day of treading the city concrete.
















































